==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ensample
<hw>En*sam"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>ensample</ets>, <ets>essample</ets>, F. <ets>exemple</ets>. See
<er>Example</er>.]</ety> <def>An example; a pattern or model for
imitation.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Tyndale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Being <qex>ensamples</qex> to the flock.</q> <rj><qau>1 Pet. v.
3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ensample</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ensample
<hw>En*sam"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To exemplify, to
show by example.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ensanguine</ent>⟦br⟧
